<h3><strong>How are millimeters to inches calculated?</strong></h3>
<p>For the conversion of <strong>millimeters (mm) to inches (in)</strong>, =
the formula is simple: <strong>inches =3D millimeters / 25.4</strong> where=
 the equivalence would be: <strong>1 millimeter is equal to 0.0393701 inche=
s</strong>. If you have the distance in millimeters, you just need to multi=
ply it by 0.0393701 to get its value in inches.</p>
